Game design Phase 5: randomization wiring + live relationship ledger

Persona jitter (Part 4, layer 2): pickPersona/dealCounterparties take a session-seed salt, so the SAME
property draws a different seller/broker personality across playthroughs (stable within a session).
Threaded through the LOI panel and the napkin counterparties card.

Branch-weight jitter (Part 4, layer 3): ScenarioRunner now jitters each branch's odds +/-15% per session
(seeded), so identical decisions diverge across runs.

Relationships are now live: closing the LOI clean records a broker 'closed-clean'; a C2C retrade records
'retraded' (broker standing drops, sellers stiffen next time); an 80+ closing records a 'closed-clean'
with the seller. Deal DNA captures broker/seller personas, broker rep at LOI, PSA catch score, and
closing score. New RelationshipLedger panel (TopBar, game mode): per-counterparty score, unlocked
behaviors, and recent interactions.

Tests: +3 (54 total) on persona jitter (stable per salt, varies across sessions).

Game design phases 1-5 complete: onboarding+profiles, coach, UW scoring, LOI/PSA, C2C deck, AM quarterly
cards, calibration review + player model, and the full randomization + relationship feedback loop.

